<h2 style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1em; font-family: arial,sans-serif;">What's new on Design @ IBM</h2>
<!----------------------------------------------------What's new entry divider-------------------------------------------------------->
<div class="ibm-container ibm-portrait-module">
<h2>Featured</h2>
<div class="ibm-container-body">

<div style="float: left; width: 90px; padding-top:5px; padding-bottom: 5px;">
	<img src="images/worldsquare_90x90.JPG" width="90" height="90" alt="world usability day logo"/>
</div>
<div style="float: right; width: 425px;padding-top: 5px; padding-bottom: 10px;">
<h3>World Usability Day 2010 Webcast: Social Media in the Workplace</h3>
<p>Social media has seen explosive growth over the past few years - Facebook has over 500 million users worldwide and Twitter is on target for 200 million users by year-end, But how does social media fit into the workplace? Could it totally replace email as the primary means of communication and collaboration? </p>
<p class="ibm-ind-link"></p>


<ul class="ibm-link-list" style="margin-left: 10px">
			<li><a class="ibm-popup-link" href="#" onclick="javascript:window.open('wud2010/IBMWorldUsabilityDayWebcast2010.html', '_blank', 'height=579,width=820,screenX=30,screenY=20,top=20,left=30,status=no,location=no,toolbar=no,directories=no,menubar=no,resizable=no,scrollbars=auto'); return false">Watch the replay</a></li>
			<li><a class="ibm-pdf-link" href="wud2010/IBMWorldUsabilityDayWebcast.pdf" target="_blank">Download the presentation slides</a></li>
		</ul>

</div>
<div class="ibm-rule"><hr></div>
	
